    <statement>
       
                <p>
                    Dennis recently had some financial trouble, and as a result they had to borrow $2,700 in the form of a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of 9%. They plan to pay the loan off in one large payment after 8 months.
                    <ol>
                        <li> How much interest does the loan generate over the 8 months? </li>
                        <li> How much will Dennis have to pay off at the end of the loan?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>         
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li> The loan generates $162.0 in interest.</li>
                <li> They will need to pay $2,862.0 at the end of the loan.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
